<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest  is called '<span class="yellow">The Mountain Wild</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">120</span> to <span class="yellow">179</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/647">Lord Agrippa</a> [<a href="/area/48">Runic Castle</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

The wilds around mountains have long been home to creatures of all sorts,<br />
types and genders.  With our population expanding, we need to look to new<br />
places to build cities and towns.  Please scout out these regional mountain<br />
areas, and decide if the animals are too fierce for us to domesticate side. <br />
When you believe you have found most of these elusive animals, please report<br />
back to me with haste.  May the powers guide you!<br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">65</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">5</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">23,000</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">15,000</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">170</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

The Mountain Wild consists of:<br />


